    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's definitely a capacitor i think. i've heard people call these electrical glitches 'gremlins' before which sounds kinda funny but i just want to know if i can try to swap it out myself or if i'll get fried. what specifically should i look for when i open the panel?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If you're confident it's a capacitor issue, you can try swapping it yourself, but exercise caution. Before opening the panel, make sure it's cool and unplugged, and consult your AC's manual for specific instructions. When you open the panel, look for the capacitor, which is usually an electrolytic capacitor with a yellow or orange stripe. It's usually held in place by screws or clips, and you'll likely see a replacement capacitor with an identical rating nearby.",
